      <arrangement id="aspace_a8cae9a3652df3ce6b8fc5c508d7c4ba">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged into three series: I. Photographic prints, 1972-1986. II. Correspondence and clippings, 1979-1987. III. Flyers and other ephemera, 1982-1987.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9685ad7164f3f0f7350a795c27a64258">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Brian McStotts (1957-2023) was a photographer who grew up surfing the beaches of Southern California. He captured the essence of surf culture in a his images taken during the 1970s-80s. Many of his photographs feature intricate details of surfers--riding the waves of Manhattan Beach and beyond--with the purpose of capturing the unique world of life on the ocean.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_189dabb16f82d896e2c1ef963d192983">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Western US surfing ephemera collection. Yale Collection of Western Americana, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d625f15ae30e67eea957a11e2a545ce2">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>The Western US surfing ephemera collection includes photographic prints taken by surfer and photographer Brian McStotts. These images of surfers were captured primarily off Manhattan Beach Pier, among other popular surfing spots.</p>
         <p>The collection also contains correspondence, announcements, clippings, decals, and other printed material related to surfing competitions, film festivals, and other activities. Also included are mailers for events and competitions from the South Bay Longboard Association and the Dapper Dann Surfing Association, along with announcements from the Manhattan Beach Cultural Arts Committee and the Old Wave Surfing Association.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_b4ee8ebdfb574ce2dc7fd9079ff7bc4f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>The Western US surfing ephemera collection is the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>
      </userestrict>
